    ],
    "http://schema.org/name": [
      {
        "@value": "She, Is Me"
      }
    ],
    "http://schema.org/description": [
      {
        "@value": "<p>Returning from the Island Fringe Festival, <b>She, Is Me</b> is a theatrical dance show that displays the diverse perspectives of women in the dance industry, trying to find balance through the chaos of reality. Through movement, song and spoken word, audiences will witness each dancer's journey, showing their uniqueness, similarities, struggles and triumphs, featuring a combination of dance styles that best represent their story. </p>\n\n<p>This content references grief, misogyny, and both physical and mental health struggles, which may be distressing. This content also references growth, power and inclusion. <b>Suitable for all ages. </p>\n\n<p>Written & Directed by Dawn Ward-Dames. </b></p>\n\n<p>Show ends at 9:00pm. There is a 15 minute intermission</p>\n"
      }
    ],
